Amazon.ca Product Description

Chauncey Billups has been an NBA stalwart since 1997. Billups, a first round draft pick of the Boston Celtics in 1997. Billups bounced around until he laded with the Pistons in 2002. He helped Detroit win the 2004 NBA Finals over the Los Angeles Lakers, four games to one. He averaged 21 points and 5.2 assists per game during the series to earn the NBA Finals MVP Award. Billups was traded to the Knicks in February 2011, and looks to anchor the back court and help them make a Playoff run for the first time since 2004. Chauncey Billups has hand signed this 8x10 photograph, which comes complete with a Steiner Sports Certificate of Authenticity.
